100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 5, 1926, British Prime Minister Stanley Baldwin announced a new government initiative to address the ongoing economic challenges facing the nation, including high unemployment and industrial strife. In the United States, a major winter storm impacted the Midwest, causing travel disruptions and power outages. Meanwhile, in Germany, tensions rose as the Weimar Republic continued to grapple with hyperinflation and political instability.
